    <div class="documentBody">
        <div>
            <p>Appointed state secretary in Ministry of Government Administration and Reform, 23 October 2009. </p>
<h2>Political positions</h2>
<p>1994 – 1996 Political adviser for the Prime Minister (Gro Harlem Brundtland)<br />1990 – 1992 Political adviser for the Minister of international development (Grete Faremo)<br />1987 – 1989 Research secretary, Labour Party <br />1987 – 1987 Group secretary, Labour Party group, Oslo municipal council <br />Several elected positions in student and political youth organisations<br />Board member of the Labour Party women’s organisation&nbsp; </p>
<h2>Professional experience<br /></h2>
<p>2006 - 2009 Head of division, Ministry of Government Administration and Reform <br />2005 – 2006 Head of research, Institute of Transport Economics<br />1997 – 2005 Researcher, Institute of Transport Economics<br />1993 – 1994 Research fellow, Fridtjof Nansen Institute<br />1984 – 1994 Journalist</p>
<h2>Education</h2>
<p>1997&nbsp; Cand Polit, Graduate degree in political science with social economics and sociology, University of Oslo.</p>
<h2>Publications:</h2>
<p>Co-author of white paper to the Storting (Parliament) in 2003 and 2009.</p>
<h2>Publications in English:</h2>
<p>Book articles:</p>
<ul>
<li>Tore Sager and Inger-Anne Ravlum (2005): ”Inter-agency Transport</li>
<li>Planning: Cooperation in a Loose Network” in The Network Society. A Context for Planning, Routledge.</li></ul>
<p>Articles in research magazines: </p>
<ul>
<li>Tore Sager and Inger-Anne Ravlum (2005): ”From projects to strategies: A transaction cost approach to politicians’ problems with strategic transport planning”. Planning Theory &amp; Practice, 2005, Vol 6.2, pp 213-232. Routledge.</li>
<li>Tore Sager and Inger-Anne Ravlum (2005): ”The Political Relevance of Planner’s Analysis: The Case of a Parliamentary Standing Committee”, Planning Theory, 2005, Vol 4(1), pp 33-65. Sage.</li>
<li>Tore Sager and Inger-Anne Ravlum (2004): ”Interagency Transport-Planning. Co-ordination and Governance Structures”, Planning Theory &amp; Practice, 2004, Vol 5, pp 171-195. Routledge.</li></ul>
<p>A number of research articles in Norwegian. <br /></p>
